        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>6. Queen Anne St | W</placeName>
                    <date>March 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have just been very much pleased by your note.</p>
<p>Four hundred guineas is a splendid sum &amp; it delights my avaritious soul.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I shall not now grudge spending money for aid in my new Book.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>With sincere thanks | My dear Sir | Yours very faithfully | Ch. Darwin—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5972.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 3 March [1868]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5972.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 3 March [1868]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD refers to <hi rend="italic">Descent.</hi></note>
